cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with learning word embeddings from visual co-occurrences, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also extensively uses large-scale visual databases like VisualGenome and ImageNet, indicating a strong connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a log-bilinear model for encoding word meanings suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the embeddings on downstream applications, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
